  "eprint": {
    "title": "Attacking Poseidon via Graeffe-Based Root-Finding over NTT-Friendly Fields",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Antonio Sanso",
        "email": "sanso@ethereum",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Giuseppe Vitto",
        "email": "orggiuseppe@zircuit",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "This paper explores the algebraic structure of the Poseidon and Poseidon2 permutations\r\nover NTT-friendly finite fields, with a focus on preimage recovery via root-finding\r\ntechniques. We introduce an algorithm for efficiently identifying single roots of high-degree\r\nunivariate polynomials that emerge from these constructions, based on the Graeffe transform\r\nand the tangent Graeffe method. Our approach is evaluated on reduced-round bounty\r\ninstances of these permutations at various security levels, as proposed by the Ethereum\r\nFoundation, demonstrating practical effectiveness. These results yield new insights into the\r\nsecurity of permutation-based cryptographic primitives instantiated over NTT-friendly prime\r\nfields.",
